</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17
</SO>
<CO>
   ABS
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
FOOD RETAILERS AND WHOLESALERS, CONVENIENCE STORES (FDR)
</IN>
<LP>
   BOISE, Idaho -- Albertson's Inc. reported net income
increased 16% to $52.9 million, or 40 cents a share, for its
second quarter ended Aug. 2.
   Sales rose 14% to $2.07 billion, although year-earlier
results were slightly depressed by a strike by workers at 34
of its stores in the Seattle, Wash., area. The company
estimated that sales would have increased by only 7.7% if the
strike had not occurred.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the year-earlier period, the company earned $45.6
million, or 34 cents a share, on sales of $1.8 billion.
   Albertson's operates 523 grocery stores in 16 states.
