</HL>
<DATE>
08/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   PARIS -- France's unemployment rate was unchanged in July
at 8.9%, the Labor Ministry said.
   The number of job-seekers stood at 2,507,600 on a
seasonally adjusted basis at the end of last month, down 0.2%
from a month before and down 1.2% from July 1989.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   On an unadjusted basis, the number of job-seekers in July
rose 2.4% from June to 2,409,600, but was still 1.2% below
the July 1989 level.
