loss of $86,000, or one cent a share, compared with net
income of $531,000, or four cents a share, in the
year-earlier period. Revenue fell 24% to $6.8 million from
$8.9 million. Officials have said, however, that they expect
third-quarter results to turn around.
   In over-the-counter trading yesterday, Steve's Homemade
shares were quoted at $1.0625, unchanged.
