<LP>
   Roussel-Uclaf S.A., the French company that makes the
abortion pill RU 486, reported a 24% increase in consolidated
profit for the first half of 1990 to 319 million francs
($60.9 million) from 258 million francs the previous year.
   The pharmaceutical group, which is 54.5% controlled by
